sequenceDiagram
  %% Diagram 52: WebSocket Event Architecture and Reconnect Flow

  autonumber
  actor C as Client
  participant WS as WebSocket Gateway
  participant Auth as Auth Guard
  participant Rooms as Room Router
  participant Presence as Presence and Session Store
  participant Cursor as Last Event Cursor Store
  participant Bus as Event Sources

  C->>WS: Connect with token + last_event_id
  WS->>Auth: Validate token and role scope
  Auth-->>WS: Auth context
  WS->>Rooms: Join role/context rooms
  WS->>Presence: Register session metadata and online state

  Bus->>WS: Publish order-status/chat/alert/live-viewer events
  WS->>C: Push event with sequence_id
  C-->>WS: Ack sequence_id
  WS->>Cursor: Persist last acked event id

  alt Ack timeout
    WS->>C: Retry unacked event with bounded retries
  end

  alt Connection drops
    C->>WS: Reconnect with exponential backoff
    WS->>Auth: Revalidate token or refresh session
    WS->>Rooms: Rejoin prior rooms by context
    WS->>C: Replay missed events since last_event_id
  end
